          <p>The actual tax bill is the same in both Section 216 scenarios (~$600). The difference is cash flow. Without the NR6, you are lending the CRA an extra $8,250 per year and waiting months to get it back. With the NR6, your monthly withholding is just $63, which is close to what you actually owe.</p>

